Variable selection

data_set = c("Years of Potential Life Lost Rate",
               "% Fair or Poor Health",
               "% Low Birthweight",
               "% Adults with Obesity",
               "% Excessive Drinking",
               "High School Graduation Rate",
               "% Unemployed",
               "Annual Average Violent Crimes",
               "Presence of Water Violation",
               "% Frequent Physical Distress",
               "HIV Prevalence Rate",
               "% Limited Access to Healthy Foods",
               "Median Household Income",
               "% Homeowners")

final_df = subset(temp_DF, select = data_set)
names(final_df) = c("YPLLRate","HealthPoorPct","LBWPct","ObeseAdultsPct","DrinkExcPct",
                    "HSGradRate","UnemployedPct","ViolsCrimeAnlAvg","WaterViol",
                    "DistressFreqPhysPct","HIVRate","FoodHealthLimAccPct",
                    "IncHousehldMedian","HomeownersPct")
final_df = na.omit(final_df)
final_df$`WaterViol` = as.factor(final_df$`WaterViol`)

#split into test and train data
indexes = sample(nrow(final_df), nrow(final_df)/2)
train_df = final_df[indexes,]
test_df = final_df[-indexes,]

Model with all predictors

#create a model with all predictors
test_model = lm(YPLLRate ~ . , data = test_df)

Fitted versus Residuals Plot

plot(fitted(test_model), resid(test_model), col = "grey", pch = 20,
     xlab = "Fitted", ylab = "Residuals", main = "Test Model 1")
abline(h = 0, col = "darkorange", lwd = 2)

hist(resid(test_model),
     xlab   = "Residuals",
     main   = "Histogram of Residuals, Test Model 1",
     col    = "darkorange",
     border = "dodgerblue",
     breaks = 45)

qqnorm(resid(test_model), main = "Normal Q-Q Plot, test_model", col = "darkgrey")
qqline(resid(test_model), col = "dodgerblue", lwd = 2)

(back_aic_mod = step(test_model, direction = "backward", trace=0))
